   in September 1992. Rates for decay class 1-2 western hemlock logs were
   greater than those from the forest floor, which ranged from 3.42 to 7.13
   g CO2.m(-2).day(-1). Respiration rates were depressed in late July and
   August compared with fall and spring owing to the summer drought
   characteristic of the Pacific Northwest. Large-diameter western hemlock
